Czech Central Bank’s Hampl Opposes EU Bank Tax, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-06-22T05:57:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/czech-central-bank-s-hampl-opposes-eu-bank-tax-hospodarske-says.html
The Czech Republic should maintain
its reservations to European Union plans to introduce taxes on
banks,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing central bank Vice-
Governor Mojmir Hampl.  Proposals to apply taxes to financial transactions or
financial operations may hurt banks’ ability to compete, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at   placa@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  